==English==
===Phrasal verb===
'''[[to]] [[come]] [[to]] [[a]] [[head]]'''
#{{idiom}} to suddenly reveal something which has been brewing beneath the surface for awhile
#:''A persons long-brewing anger has '''come to a head'''.''

===Background===
The [[etymology]] is possibly related to acne,      
where the '''head''' of the pimple forms after something bad has been going on beneath the surface.